		</td></tr>
		
	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=119683'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#3399FF;font-weight:bold; '>Heimdall-RN</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Champion<br>
			
				Posts: 1294<br>
				
				Registered: 10-14-2005
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=119683'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/warrior.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=14273#M14273">1</a> of 481
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1510 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		
				background-color: #050A0E; 
				
				 background-image: none;
				 
				background-repeat: repeat-x;
				" 
			>
			<div>If each fight lasts ~40 seconds, mob Triples, hits 66% of the time, every 2 seconds, mob gets a hit once a second, so warrior negates 1 DI per second.</div><div></div><div>Paladin Heals</div><div></div><div>Touch of Piety is 1714 pre-focus and pre AA... post focus average its 2050. 1 cast per 40 second fight alone is equal to a -1DI of about 51. DB 1 DI 51=1021 max hits. So any mob with a max hit of 1020 or less a pally tanks better than a warrior casting 1 heal per 40 second fight. 2 Heals raises the DI to 102(2041 Max hit) My shaman twink can drop 2K mana pre-AA/Spec/Focusper fight and stay up in mana during most grind groups until bathroom breaks, respawn pauses, etc. 2 stuns- Ancient Force of Jeron, Force of Piety, and 2 casts of Touch of Piety is 1302 mana pre-AA/Focus/Specialization. 2 Pained Memory, and half of Canni V will net my shaman back about 1253 mana per fight, but also require another 420 spent, so a net return of 833 for a net spent during a fight of about 1170.</div><p></p><p>Shadowknight Taps</p><p>Ancient Bite of Muram Recourse- +135 mana, Inruku's Bite recourse +130 mana. 265 mana per fight cast, IF both are cast once per fight, after 1.5 fights a cleric will have what ammounts to a mana free CH to cast. , that means for 9600hp to even EQUAL -1DI, You're looking at a DI of 160 - (DB1 DI 160 max hit 3201)</p><p>So 2 Bite recourses to a cleric willflat out DESTROY-1DI in non-defensive content.... Requireing at minimum a mob with a DI of 160. Two Paladin heals will negate -1DI requiring a DI of 102 or better. To be completely fair, a fight will be marginally shorter with a warrior tanking than a paladin tanking depending on how long it takes the DPS classes to ramp up with the initial snap agro availability, plus of course (for an SK)the bonus mana for a DD class being able to get another DD in (essentially mana free) every so often. (Time/Damage varies on class, AA, and Focus)</p><p></p><p>What this basically means isn't that knights are broken, what it means is:</p><ul><li>Paladins probably need a minor boost.</li><li>-1DI hasn't scaled at all similar to the increase in spell efficiency</li><li>This should probably be looked at.</li><li>Whatever solution is chosen should be a long term self scaling solution that isn't Expanion era or mob DPS dependant.</li><li>-1DI is the part that's broken, not Paladin heals, or SK Taps.</li></ul>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>02-25-2006</span> <span class=time_text>09:59 AM</span>
		</span>
