		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div>It's long been the case that SK and warrior abilities scale pretty much inversely to each other.<br><br>Warrior superior mitigation matters a lot vs very difficult mobs.&nbsp; It doesn't matter much at all vs a green or light blue mob.<br><br>SK taps, procs, etc can completely negate damage on very weak mobs, but really don't do jack against tough ones.<br><div></div><br>Pally abilities have a lot more upward scaling.... to the point that stuns stop working, then they just have heals to fall back on.&nbsp; Pretty good, until they go oom, so it's not really a sustained advantage.<br><br>Easiest thing to do to give warriors something that scales downward?&nbsp; rework shocking defense so it's actually useful... more of an aura type ability, in the spirit of the new PoR pally/SK defensive procs.&nbsp; Perhaps even ditch the stun idea completely for a rune, a mitigation buff, something that negates some portion of incoming mob damage.&nbsp; There would have to be an endurance cost for the ability, but it would let you trade end for downward scaling superior defense.<br><p>Message Edited by josahd on <span class=date_text>02-25-2006</span> <span class=time_text>01:12 PM</span>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=175692" target=new>Josahd, Scourge Knight</a>
							</div>
								
