		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Heimdall, please take a look at lucy on that paladin heal you listed. Check something valuable to a knight, something called a cast time. Better yet, I did it for you. I am betting you looked at the spell but didnt check the cast time, but its 3.75 second cast time. This can be lowered by spell haste items to around 2.75 second cast time or so, dont remember exactly. But the main point is even 2 seconds is a long time when facing a mob, and counting on this spell is a futile effort, as any mob that is challening enough to us to make paladins use this spell would be interrupted, or pushed, before it got off. It doesnt take much to interrupt a knight, even the slightest little push does the trick.<br><br>So for fairness in future posts, please use light of piety, a 1234 base heal. This is the heal you will see paladins use. Only time touch of piety comes into play is on rare occasions where a paladin isnt tanking and needs to keep people healed, mainly raids. Also take into account that light of piety is a worse hp to mana ratio than touch of piety, and has a longer refresh time than normal spells where touch of piety is normal spell refresh time.<br><br>	
