			Autoparry/riposte have nothing to do with the content of this thread though.&nbsp; I didn't ask for it; the OP didn't say anything about it.&nbsp; Like I said, the thread isn't about knight upgrades.<br><br>And no one claimed knights need adjustment here, either.&nbsp; You just threw that in there.... just because?<br><div></div><br>Shields/shield block do not downward scale.&nbsp; Downward scaling abilities are say... something like a lifetap proc that provides you a fixed amount of healing regardless of what a mob is hitting you for, where if the mob is doing little damage, it can offset the entire mob's damage output, or if the mob is doing insane damage, the amount healed becomes fairly negligable.&nbsp; Or a casted heal that can completely negate damage from that light blue con, indefinitely, but will shave off 1 hit, or less, vs a difficult mob, and quickly run the pally oom.&nbsp; That's downard scaling.... abilities that by nature dominate weak content, give us parity in appropriate group content, and fall behind against very difficult content.<br><br>What I posted- possibly rework shocking defense into something that can be frequently reused, and actually shaves off a good portion of damage, is something that downward scales.<br>
